<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 4:15PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central Hill
and north central Chouteau Counties through 500 PM MDT...
At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles west of Box Elder, or 15 miles northwest of Big Sandy, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Big Sandy, Box Elder, Boneau, Azure and Sangrey.
This includes Highway 87 between mile markers 77 and 94.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
